FuncDef:
The active nat64 vsuf command enables the NAT64 function on a specified service board.
The undo active nat64 vsuf command disables the NAT64 function on a specified service board.
By default, The NAT64 function is disabled on a service board.

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies the slot ID of a service board.
The value is a string of 1 to 15 case-sensitive characters, spaces not supported.

ExtraInfo:
To enable the NAT64 function on a service board, run the active nat64 vsuf command. The NAT64 function is under license control.
If a service board is Down or fails to be detected, the service board does not automatically release NAT64 license resources. To release the license resources, run the undo active nat64 vsuf command.
